---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Create a Shopify FAQ page for EasyEdit"
  description="Step-by-step guide to creating a FAQ page on your Shopify store to help customers understand how to edit their orders after purchase."
>
  <main class="space-y-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-8 lg:px-3 lg:py-16">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="mb-8 flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <a href="/help" class="hover:text-[#6d28d9]">Help Center</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-900">Create a Shopify FAQ page</span
        >
      </nav>

      <!-- Article Header -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#6d28d9]/10 px-4 py-1">
          <span class="text-sm font-medium text-[#6d28d9]">Getting Started</span
          >
        </div>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl leading-tight font-bold md:text-5xl">
          How to create a Shopify FAQ page for EasyEdit
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Help your customers understand how they can edit their orders right
          after placing them with a clear and helpful FAQ page.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Why Create a FAQ Page?</h2>
        <p>
          A well-crafted FAQ page helps your customers understand the
          self-service order editing capabilities available to them. This
          reduces support tickets, improves customer satisfaction, and empowers
          customers to manage their orders independently.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Step 1: Access Your Shopify Admin
        </h2>
        <p>
          Log in to your Shopify admin panel and navigate to <strong
            >Online Store > Pages</strong
          > in the left sidebar.
        </p>

        <div
          class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-[#6d28d9]/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <svg
              class="mt-1 mr-3 h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 text-[#6d28d9]"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-[#6d28d9]">Pro Tip</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                If you already have a FAQ page, you can simply add these
                questions to your existing page instead of creating a new one.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Step 2: Create a New Page
        </h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>Click the "Add page" button in the top right corner</li>
          <li>
            Enter a title for your page (e.g., "Order Editing FAQ" or "How to
            Edit Your Order")
          </li>
          <li>
            Add a brief introduction explaining that customers can edit their
            orders after purchase
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Step 3: Add Essential FAQ Questions
        </h2>
        <p>
          Include these key questions and answers to help your customers
          understand the order editing process:
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: Can I edit my order after placing it?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> Yes! You can edit your order within [timeframe]
              of placing it. You can modify items, update quantities, change your
              shipping address, or cancel your order before it ships.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: How do I edit my order?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> After placing your order, check your email for
              the order confirmation. Click the "Edit Order" button or link in the
              email to access your order details and make changes. You can also access
              the order editor from the order status page.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: What changes can I make to my order?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> You can:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700">
              <li>Add or remove items</li>
              <li>Change product quantities</li>
              <li>Update your shipping address</li>
              <li>Swap products for different variants (size, color, etc.)</li>
              <li>Cancel your order entirely</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: How long do I have to edit my order?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> You can edit your order until it has been shipped.
              Typically, orders can be modified within [X hours/days] of purchase.
              Once an order has shipped, you'll need to follow our return process
              instead.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: Will I be charged extra if I add items?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> If you add items or increase quantities, you'll
              see the updated total and will be charged the difference. If you remove
              items or reduce quantities, you'll receive a refund for the difference
              to your original payment method.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
              Q: What if my order has already shipped?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>A:</strong> Once your order has shipped, you can no longer
              edit it through the order editor. Please refer to our return and exchange
              policy, or contact our customer support team for assistance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Step 4: Customize for Your Store
        </h2>
        <p>
          Make sure to customize the answers above based on your specific store
          policies:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            Replace [timeframe] and [X hours/days] with your actual time limits
          </li>
          <li>
            Add any specific restrictions or limitations for your store (e.g.,
            certain products can't be edited)
          </li>
          <li>Include links to your return policy or customer support</li>
          <li>Add information about any fees or restrictions that apply</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Step 5: Publish and Link to Your FAQ Page
        </h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>Click "Save" to publish your FAQ page</li>
          <li>
            Add a link to your FAQ page in your main navigation menu or footer
          </li>
          <li>
            Consider adding a link to the FAQ in your order confirmation emails
          </li>
          <li>
            Reference the FAQ page in your EasyEdit widget configuration for
            easy customer access
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <svg
              class="mt-1 mr-3 h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 text-green-600"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-green-900">Best Practice</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-green-800">
                Include a clear call-to-action on your FAQ page that links
                directly to where customers can check their order status and
                make edits. This reduces friction and improves the customer
                experience.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Additional Tips</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            Use clear, simple language that's easy for all customers to
            understand
          </li>
          <li>
            Add screenshots or a short video showing the order editing process
          </li>
          <li>
            Keep the page updated as you modify your order editing policies
          </li>
          <li>
            Monitor customer support tickets to identify additional questions to
            add
          </li>
          <li>
            Consider adding a search function if your FAQ page grows large
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Need More Help?</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about setting up order editing capabilities on
          your Shopify store or configuring EasyEdit, our support team is here
          to help.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles Section (for future) -->
      <!-- <div class="mt-16 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-8">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-semibold">Related Articles</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          Future related articles will go here
        </div>
      </div> -->

      <!-- Contact Support CTA -->
      <div class="mt-16 rounded-xl bg-[#6d28d9]/5 p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Still have questions?</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-600">
          Our support team is ready to help you set up your FAQ page and answer
          any questions.
        </p>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row"
        >
          <a
            href="/#contact"
            class="inline-flex rounded-xl bg-[#6d28d9] px-8 py-4 text-lg font-normal text-white shadow-lg duration-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-[#5a1fb8] hover:shadow-xl"
          >
            Contact Support
          </a>
          <a
            href="/help"
            class="inline-flex rounded-xl border border-gray-300 bg-white px-8 py-4 text-lg font-normal text-gray-900 shadow-sm duration-200 hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-md"
          >
            Back to Help Center
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
